Description: Provides quality checks for MEDITS trawl survey exchange data
    tables (TA, TB, TC, TE, TL). The main function RoME() calls all check
    functions in a defined sequence to perform a complete quality control of
    TX data, including header validation, controlled-vocabulary checks,
    cross-table consistency tests, and biological plausibility checks. No
    automatic correction is applied: the package detects errors, warns the
    user, and specifies the type of error to ease data correction. Checks
    can be run simultaneously on multi-year datasets. An embedded Shiny
    application is also provided via run_RoME_app().
